{
  "stem": "1603.4",
  "chunk_idx": 0,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And I want to make a point as to-- to-- with the story that-- that would explain the food problem and the water problem.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So-- because the water pipes were bombed away and so on, there was no water, so to speak.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "We melted snow, and we also kept water in the bathtub.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And from the bathtub, we boiled water.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And then later on it was cooling off, and we were drinking it as drinking water or cooked with it.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "So that was our water.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "The food was that we were able to exchange for various of things, of jewelry or money, whatever, to get some flour and some potatoes and a little fat or something and a little yeast.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "So my mother was able to hand-make bread and then bake it.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "So mostly we survived on, as you say, bread and water and on various things.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "It was very cold weather, and the Germans had horses to-- to pull the heavy artillery on the streets.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And naturally then the airplanes came and threw the bombs and killed the horses.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "So we looked out on the street, and here were a frozen, dead horses.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So somebody would go out with a saw and saw the leg off of the horse and part of the leg and then would bring it in and then, as you call it, defrost that leg and they would cook that horse leg, and we would eat it.",
      "word_count": 48
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And it was like a heavenly meal.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And so I can tell you that horse meat is a little sweet, but it was fantastic.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And with how hungry we were, one time we found some canned food.",
      "word_count": 13
    }
  ],
